UML:TaggedValue.value: Extends EOP EarthObservationEquipment for Limb Looking products.
Extends EOP footprint for limb looking profiles
Upper bound of measurements in vertical dimension. Must be gml Measure
Lower bound of measurements in vertical dimension. Must be gml Measure

A geometry of type GM_Multicurve is used to define the nominal track on the earths surface. This track is essentially a line that is representative of the product but does not include points for every value. The use of GM_MultiCurve allows for multiple lines and breaks in lines.
A set of unstructured occultation points (e.g. with non-astronomical bodies like GPS satellites) at which atmospheric profiles are available within the product.
Extends EOP Sensor for Limb Looking products.
xtension of eop:Acquisition, extended for LMB to add observation mode.

Observation mode used in acquisition. e.g 'UTLS-1' is one of the seven MIPAS observation modes which determine the sampling regime. Not constrained to codelist at the limb-looking level as these modes are instrument specific.
Extends eop:EarthObservation for Limb Looking products
